reviews.text:
Very neat Vietnamese Restaurant. The service was quite good and friendly, and consi6the location, it was nice that some of the staff spoke English.
The food was typical for such pho restaurants. It was served quite fast and fresh.
Not bad! It can be quite pack during lunch hours.

Came for simple and nice dinner. Place not so fancy but clean and tidy. Food is good and price is reasonable. We ordered the beef pho and Viet steam roll. The hot fun is nice tender and have a smooth texture. Broth is not so light but fresh and very tasty. Portion is reasonable. Would definitely came back to try others.
